  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing requirement mandates a controlled-experiment verification method; the supporting validation activity is extensively documented and cited in the narrative as providing direct mechanical characterisation of the construct, with bilateral laboratory participation, pre-specified acceptance bounds, and a structured comparison protocol — conditions that closely resemble a controlled experiment. The activity record, however, is classified as an observational-study in its structured metadata, reflecting that randomisation and blinding procedures were not formally implemented and specimen selection was non-randomised. Because the narrative treats the two characterisations as equivalent, the inference link between the requirement's required verification method and the activity's activityType is broken.",
